news.title: Nagpur: With three days notice, NIT razes 35 shops before businesses shift into mall
news.para: ​Then, even before the deadline ended to shift his business to a shop in the mall, a team of civic officials, policemen, and staffers of the mall builder — Pune-based Goel Ganga Infrastructure and Real Estate Private Ltd — demolished the shop on Monday morning, causing huge financial loss to Gala.

news.title: Hyderabad's new master plan to cover 84 villages of GO 111
news.para: The new master plan will bring 84 villages that came under GO 111, catchment areas of Himayatsagar and Osmansagar reservoirs under its ambit.

news.title: Nod to gates with night-vision cameras at seven licensed colonies in Gurugram
news.para: These colonies are Ardee City B Block, DLF phases I, II & V, blocks C of Sushant Lok I, II & III. Another colony, Experion Society in Sector 112, which also sought permission for installing gates, has, however, been refused the same.

news.title: Jaipur: 1,327 lease deeds sanctioned on first day of Shahar camp
news.para: On the first day, the civic body issued a total of 1327 lease deeds to the plot owners. As per the records, 1102 free hold lease deeds and 225 lease deeds were issued on May 2.

news.title: Nashik civic body sets April property tax collection record
news.para: Earlier, the highest property tax collection of the NMC was Rs 15 crore in April 2019. In April 2022, the NMC had collected only Rs 7 crore through property tax.

news.title: Hill cut, trees cleared for hotel at Arpora, will file FIR against PDA officers: Goa forest minister
news.para: “Today morning, deputy conservator of forest, North, inspected the construction site at Hotel Park Regis in Arpora. During his inspection, massive hill cutting was noticed with no permission for the same. Section 8 of the Goa Preservation of Trees Act, 1984, classifies it as a serious offence,” Rane said.

news.title: Embassy Office Parks REIT, Hilton to develop hotels in Bengaluru
news.para: The upcoming dual-branded hotel will include two hotels - a Hilton Hotels & Resorts brand hotel and a Hilton Garden Inn brand hotel and will come up in Embassy Tech Village (ETV) —owned by Embassy REIT—in Bangalore’s Outer Ring Road.

news.title: Cricketer Prithvi Shaw buys Rs 10.5-crore apartment on Bandra Reclamation in Mumbai
news.para: The 22-year-old cricketer has purchased the apartment from Pyramid Developers and Ultra Lifespace, developers of the project. He could not be reached immediately for a comment.

news.title: Edelweiss Housing Finance raises Rs 276 crore
news.para: ​The public issue of secured redeemable non-convertible debentures (NCDs) has been successfully completed and the company has allotted 27,59,057 NCDs of the face value of Rs 1,000 each, amounting to Rs 275.91 crore, the company said in a release.

news.title: Bengaluru: 12 years on, bank told to refund bidder Rs 24.1 lakh with 8% interest
news.para: Babu had shown interest in purchasing a property at Nayandahalli (on Mysuru Road) that was being auctioned by the then State Bank of Mysore (now SBI).

news.title: Mumbai: Builder can't sell society parking slots, says consumer body
news.para: The society claimed all 13 parking slots were directly allotted by the builder at a cost of Rs 25,000 each and society had no role in allotment.

news.title: Realty firm TARC raises Rs 1,330 crore to repay entire loans
news.para: In a regulatory filing, TARC Ltd, formerly Anant Raj Global Ltd, informed that the company has "successfully raised Rs 1,330 crores by way of issuance of secured Non- Convertible Debentures."

news.title: L&T Finance explores exiting realty projects lending business
news.para: The company is also looking to partner with dedicated funds to create a platform which will commit funds to the infrastructure projects. This will help the company in eventually bringing down its loan book in the segment.

news.title: Australia home prices keep rising even as Sydney, Melbourne cool
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic out on Monday showed prices in the combined capital cities nudged up 0.3% in April from March, as Sydney dropped 0.2% for a second month and Melbourne held steady.

news.title: Thiruvankulam residents hit by stalled development
news.para: Similar is the case of the 15 cents of land owned by Indira. "We completed the foundation works of our dream house on my wife's property. However, we could not complete the construction,'' says Appu, Indira's husband.
